lcUpsIdentSoftwareVersion.name: lcUpsIdentSoftwareVersion
lcUpsIdentSoftwareVersion.description: The UPS SNMP Agent software version.

lcUpsIdentSpecific.name: lcUpsIdentSpecific
lcUpsIdentSpecific.description: A reference to MIB definitions specific to the particular UPS being managed. This object is used to locate the product-specific MIB for this device. If this information is not present, its value should be the OBJECT IDENTIFIER { 0 0 }, which is a syntactically valid object identifier, and any conformant implementation of ASN.1 and BER must be able to generate and recognize this value.

lcUpsIdentFirmwareVersion.name: lcUpsIdentFirmwareVersion
lcUpsIdentFirmwareVersion.description: The firmware revision level of the UPS.

lcUpsIdentSerialNumber.name: lcUpsIdentSerialNumber
lcUpsIdentSerialNumber.description: The serial number of the UPS.

lcUpsIdentManufactureDate.name: lcUpsIdentManufactureDate
lcUpsIdentManufactureDate.description: The date of manufacture of the UPS.

lcUpsBatTimeRemaining.name: lcUpsBatTimeRemaining
lcUpsBatTimeRemaining.description: The estimated time to depletion of battery charge. (Unit of measure: Minute)

lcUpsBatTemperature.name: lcUpsBatTemperature
lcUpsBatTemperature.description: The battery temperature. (Unit of measure: Degree, Centigrade)

lcUpsBatVoltage.name: lcUpsBatVoltage
lcUpsBatVoltage.description: The current battery voltage. (Unit of measure: volt)

lcUpsBatCurrent.name: lcUpsBatCurrent
lcUpsBatCurrent.description: The current battery discharging/charging current. (Unit of measure: Amp)

lcUpsBatCapacity.name: lcUpsBatCapacity
lcUpsBatCapacity.description: The current battery capacity in percentage of total available.

lcUpsBatTotalDischCounts.name: lcUpsBatTotalDischCounts
lcUpsBatTotalDischCounts.description: The number of discharges the UPS has experienced.

lcUpsBatCycleDurationInSeconds.name: lcUpsBatCycleDurationInSeconds
lcUpsBatCycleDurationInSeconds.description: The total accumulated discharge time in seconds.

lcUpsBatAmpHours.name: lcUpsBatAmpHours
lcUpsBatAmpHours.description: The number of amp hours withdrawn from battery.

lcUpsBatKWhours.name: lcUpsBatKWhours
lcUpsBatKWhours.description: The number of Kilowatt-hours withdrawn from battery.

lcUpsBatWattHours.name: lcUpsBatWattHours
lcUpsBatWattHours.description: The number of Watt-hours withdrawn from battery.

lcUpsInputFrequency.name: lcUpsInputFrequency
lcUpsInputFrequency.description: The current input frequency. (Unit of measure: Hertz)

lcUpsInputBrownOuts.name: lcUpsInputBrownOuts
lcUpsInputBrownOuts.description: The number of brown-out conditions the UPS has experienced.

lcUpsInputBlackOuts.name: lcUpsInputBlackOuts
lcUpsInputBlackOuts.description: The number of black-out conditions the UPS has experienced.

lcUpsInputTransients.name: lcUpsInputTransients
lcUpsInputTransients.description: The number of transient (surge and spike) conditions the UPS has experienced.

lcUpsInputNumLines.name: lcUpsInputNumLines
lcUpsInputNumLines.description: The number of input lines utilized in this device. This entry indicates the number of rows in the input table.

lcUpsInputVoltage.name: lcUpsInputVoltage
lcUpsInputVoltage.description: The input voltage. (Unit of measure: Volt)

lcUpsInputCurrent.name: lcUpsInputCurrent
lcUpsInputCurrent.description: The input current. (Unit of measure: Amp)

lcUpsOutputFrequency.name: lcUpsOutputFrequency
lcUpsOutputFrequency.description: The current output frequency. (Unit of measure: Hertz)

lcUpsOutputNumLines.name: lcUpsOutputNumLines
lcUpsOutputNumLines.description: The number of output lines utilized in this device. This entry indicates the number of rows in the output table.

lcUpsOutputVoltage.name: lcUpsOutputVoltage
lcUpsOutputVoltage.description: The output voltage. (Unit of measure: Volt)

lcUpsOutputCurrent.name: lcUpsOutputCurrent
lcUpsOutputCurrent.description: The output current. (Unit of measure: Amp)

lcUpsInverterStatus.name: lcUpsInverterStatus
lcUpsInverterStatus.description: The state of the inverter. Unknown is returned if the state can not be determined.

lcUpsInverterTemp.name: lcUpsInverterTemp
lcUpsInverterTemp.description: The temperature of the inverter. (Unit of measure: degree, Centigrade)

lcUpsAlarms.name: lcUpsAlarms
lcUpsAlarms.description: The current number of alarm conditions.

lcUpsAlarmId.name: lcUpsAlarmId
lcUpsAlarmId.description: A unique identifier for an alarm condition. This value must remain constant between agent initializations.

lcUpsAlarmDescr.name: lcUpsAlarmDescr
lcUpsAlarmDescr.description: A reference to an alarm description object. The object referenced should not be accessible, but rather be used to provide a unique description of the alarm condition.

lcUpsAlarmTime.name: lcUpsAlarmTime
lcUpsAlarmTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the alarm condition occured.

lcUpsTestBattery.name: lcUpsTestBattery
lcUpsTestBattery.description: Setting this variable to 'start' will initiate the battery test. Setting this variable to 'abort' will stop the battery test if the test is in- progress, otherwise it has no effect. Setting this variable to 'unknown' has no effect. Reading this variable will always result in a return value of 'unknown'. If 'lcUpsTestBatteryStatus' is 'failed' the test may not be performed again and the status will remain in the failure state.

lcUpsTestBatteryStatus.name: lcUpsTestBatteryStatus
lcUpsTestBatteryStatus.description: The status of the battery test.

lcUpsTestDiag.name: lcUpsTestDiag
lcUpsTestDiag.description: Setting this variable to 'start' will initiate the diagnostics test. Setting this variable to 'abort' will stop the diagnostics test if the test is in-progress, otherwise it has no effect. Setting this variable to 'unknown' has no effect. Reading this variable will always result in a return value of 'unknown'.

lcUpsTestDiagStatus.name: lcUpsTestDiagStatus
lcUpsTestDiagStatus.description: The status of the diagnostics test.

lcUpsControlOutputOffDelay.name: lcUpsControlOutputOffDelay
lcUpsControlOutputOffDelay.description: Setting this object causes the agent to instruct the UPS to turn off the output after the indicated number of seconds. The agent counts down the number of seconds until the event will take place. The agent issues an lcUpsOutputOffTrap when the countdown finishes. Note that different models have different clock resolutions, usually greater than 1 second. As a result, the command will only be accurate to the resolution of the UPS's clock. The command can be cancelled by setting lcUpsControlCancelCommand to the value cancel.

lcUpsControlOutputOnDelay.name: lcUpsControlOutputOnDelay
lcUpsControlOutputOnDelay.description: Setting this object causes the agent to instruct the UPS to turn on the output after the indicated number of seconds. The agent counts down the number of seconds until the event will take place. The agent issues an lcUpsOutputOnTrap when the countdown finishes. Note that different models have different clock resolutions, usually greater than 1 second. As a result, the command will only be accurate to the resolution of the UPS's clock. The command can be cancelled by setting lcUpsControlCancelCommand to the value cancel.

lcUpsControlOutputOffTrapDelay.name: lcUpsControlOutputOffTrapDelay
lcUpsControlOutputOffTrapDelay.description: When 'lcUpsControlOutputOffDelay' reaches a value less than or equal to this object's value, an lcUpsOutputOffWarningTrap will be produced and this object will be reset to 0.

lcUpsControlOutputOnTrapDelay.name: lcUpsControlOutputOnTrapDelay
lcUpsControlOutputOnTrapDelay.description: When 'lcUpsControlOutputOnDelay' reaches a value less than or equal to this object's value, an lcUpsOutputOnWarningTrap will be produced and this object will be reset to 0.

lcUpsControlUnixShutdownDelay.name: lcUpsControlUnixShutdownDelay
lcUpsControlUnixShutdownDelay.description: Setting this object causes the agent to instruct the UPS to perform a UNIX Shutdown in the indicated number of seconds. The agent counts down the number of seconds until the event will take place. A Unix shutdown is only valid if the UPS is on Battery. During a UNIX Shutdown, the UPS will turn off the output even if the Utility comes back on line before the shutdown time arrives. Note that different models have different clock resolutions, usually greater than 1 second. As a result, the command will only be accurate to the resolution of the UPS's clock. The command can be cancelled by setting lcUpsControlCancelCommand to the value 'cancel'.

lcUpsControlUnixShutdownTrapDelay.name: lcUpsControlUnixShutdownTrapDelay
lcUpsControlUnixShutdownTrapDelay.description: When 'lcUpsControlUnixShutdownDelay' reaches a value less than or equal to this object's value, an lcUpsUnixShutdownWarningTrap will be produced and this object will be reset to 0.

lcUpsControlCancelCommands.name: lcUpsControlCancelCommands
lcUpsControlCancelCommands.description: Setting this variable to 'cancel' will cause the agent to issue instructions to the UPS to cancel all outstanding commands, such as lcUpsControlOutputOff, lcUpsControlOutputOn, lcUpsControlUnixShutdown.

lcUpsControlRebootAgentDelay.name: lcUpsControlRebootAgentDelay
lcUpsControlRebootAgentDelay.description: Setting this object causes the agent to reboot after the indicated number of seconds have expired. The value will count down until the event takes place.

lcUpsNominalOutputVoltage.name: lcUpsNominalOutputVoltage
lcUpsNominalOutputVoltage.description: The nominal output voltage. (Unit of measure: volt)

lcUpsNominalInputVoltage.name: lcUpsNominalInputVoltage
lcUpsNominalInputVoltage.description: The nominal input voltage. (Unit of measure: volt)

lcUpsNominalOutputWatts.name: lcUpsNominalOutputWatts
lcUpsNominalOutputWatts.description: The nominal power rating. (Unit of measure: watt)

lcUpsNominalOutputFreq.name: lcUpsNominalOutputFreq
lcUpsNominalOutputFreq.description: The nominal output frequency. (Unit of measure: Hertz)

lcUpsNominalInputFreq.name: lcUpsNominalInputFreq
lcUpsNominalInputFreq.description: The nominal input frequency. (Unit of measure: Hertz)

lcUpsNominalOutputWattsRating.name: lcUpsNominalOutputWattsRating
lcUpsNominalOutputWattsRating.description: The nominal power rating. (Unit of measure: watt)

lcUpsOnBypass.name: lcUpsOnBypass
lcUpsOnBypass.description: Indicates that the UPS is currently on bypass.

lcUpsBypassFrequency.name: lcUpsBypassFrequency
lcUpsBypassFrequency.description: The current bypass frequency. (Unit of measure: Hertz)

lcUpsBypassNumLines.name: lcUpsBypassNumLines
lcUpsBypassNumLines.description: The number of bypass lines utilized in this device. This entry indicates the number of rows in the bypass table.

lcUpsBypassVoltage.name: lcUpsBypassVoltage
lcUpsBypassVoltage.description: The bypass voltage. (Unit of measure: Volt)

lcUpsBypassCurrent.name: lcUpsBypassCurrent
lcUpsBypassCurrent.description: The bypass current. (Unit of measure: Amp)

lcUpsConfigBypassInstalled.name: lcUpsConfigBypassInstalled
lcUpsConfigBypassInstalled.description: Indicates if a bypass is installed in the UPS.

lcUpsConfigModuleCount.name: lcUpsConfigModuleCount
lcUpsConfigModuleCount.description: A number identifying how many multi-module UPS are connected to the System Control Cabinet.

lcUpsConfigCurrentModule.name: lcUpsConfigCurrentModule
lcUpsConfigCurrentModule.description: A number identifying which module of a multi-module UPS is currently being monitored.

lcUpsConfigAudibleStatus.name: lcUpsConfigAudibleStatus
lcUpsConfigAudibleStatus.description: The requested state of the audible alarm. When in the disabled state, the audible alarm should never sound. The enabled state is self-describing. Setting this object to muted(3) when the audible alarm is sounding shall temporarily silence the alarm.

lcUpsConfigLowBattTime.name: lcUpsConfigLowBattTime
lcUpsConfigLowBattTime.description: The value of lcUpsBatTimeRemaining at which a lowBatteryWarning condition is declared. (Unit of measure: Minute)

lcUpsConfigAutoRestart.name: lcUpsConfigAutoRestart
lcUpsConfigAutoRestart.description: Setting this object will start the output after the indicated number of ticks (1 tick = 10 seconds), including starting the UPS, if necessary. Setting this object to 0 will cause the startup to occur immediately. Setting this object to -1 will disable autorestart.

lcUpsSwitchedReceptMaxNum.name: lcUpsSwitchedReceptMaxNum
lcUpsSwitchedReceptMaxNum.description: The maximum number of switched receptacles supported by the Ups.

lcUpsSwitchedReceptOnDelay.name: lcUpsSwitchedReceptOnDelay
lcUpsSwitchedReceptOnDelay.description: Setting this object causes the agent to instruct the UPS to turn on a receptacle after the indicated number of seconds. The agent counts down the number of seconds until the event will take place. The agent issues an lcUpsReceptOnTrap when the countdown finishes. Note that different models have different clock resolutions, usually greater than 1 second. As a result, the command will only be accurate to the resolution of the UPS's clock. The command can be cancelled by setting lcUpsSwitchedCancelCommand to the value cancel.

lcUpsSwitchedReceptOnTrapDelay.name: lcUpsSwitchedReceptOnTrapDelay
lcUpsSwitchedReceptOnTrapDelay.description: When 'lcUpsSwitchedReceptOnDelay' reaches a value less than or equal to this object's value, an lcUpsReceptOnWarningTrap will be produced and this object will be reset to 0.

lcUpsSwitchedReceptOffDelay.name: lcUpsSwitchedReceptOffDelay
lcUpsSwitchedReceptOffDelay.description: Setting this object causes the agent to instruct the UPS to turn off a receptacle after the indicated number of seconds. The agent counts down the number of seconds until the event will take place. The agent issues an lcUpsReceptOffTrap when the countdown finishes. Note that different models have different clock resolutions, usually greater than 1 second. As a result, the command will only be accurate to the resolution of the UPS's clock. The command can be cancelled by setting lcUpsSwitchedCancelCommand to the value cancel.

lcUpsSwitchedReceptOffTrapDelay.name: lcUpsSwitchedReceptOffTrapDelay
lcUpsSwitchedReceptOffTrapDelay.description: When 'lcUpsSwitchedReceptOffDelay' reaches a value less than or equal to this object's value, an lcUpsReceptOffWarningTrap will be produced and this object will be reset to 0.

lcUpsSwitchedReceptStatus.name: lcUpsSwitchedReceptStatus
lcUpsSwitchedReceptStatus.description: The status of the device receptacle. Note that some devices may support Switched of device receptacles as a group only (by using lcUpsSwitchedOutputOffDelay and lcUpsSwitchedOutputOnDelay).

lcUpsSwitchedReceptLabel.name: lcUpsSwitchedReceptLabel
lcUpsSwitchedReceptLabel.description: A user-defined text string associated with a switched receptacle. This may be used to describe the load powered from the receptacle. The text string is stored in non-volatile memory.

lcUpsOverloadWarningTrap.name: lcUpsOverloadWarningTrap
lcUpsOverloadWarningTrap.description: An lcUpsOverloadWarningTrap signifies that the UPS has detected an Overload condition where the output load has exceeded the UPS's rated capacity.

lcUpsOverloadShutdownTrap.name: lcUpsOverloadShutdownTrap
lcUpsOverloadShutdownTrap.description: An lcUpsOverloadShutdownTrap signifies that the UPS has detected an Overload condition where the output load has exceeded the UPS's rated capacity and has shut off the output.

lcUpsOnBatteryTrap.name: lcUpsOnBatteryTrap
lcUpsOnBatteryTrap.description: An lcUpsOnBatteryTrap signifies that the UPS is currently on Battery Power.

lcUpsLowBatteryWarningTrap.name: lcUpsLowBatteryWarningTrap
lcUpsLowBatteryWarningTrap.description: An lcUpsLowBatteryWarningTrap signifies that the UPS has entered a Low Battery state.

lcUpsLowBatteryShutdownTrap.name: lcUpsLowBatteryShutdownTrap
lcUpsLowBatteryShutdownTrap.description: An lcUpsLowBatteryShutdownTrap signifies that the UPS has shut off the output due to a Low Battery state.

lcUpsUtilPowerFailedTrap.name: lcUpsUtilPowerFailedTrap
lcUpsUtilPowerFailedTrap.description: An lcUpsUtilPowerFailedTrap signifies that the utility power input to the UPS has been lost.

lcUpsUtilPowerRestoredTrap.name: lcUpsUtilPowerRestoredTrap
lcUpsUtilPowerRestoredTrap.description: An lcUpsUtilPowerRestoredTrap signifies that the utility power has been restored to the UPS.

lcUpsInputOverVoltageTrap.name: lcUpsInputOverVoltageTrap
lcUpsInputOverVoltageTrap.description: An lcUpsInputOverVoltageTrap signifies that the UPS has detected a high input voltage condition.

lcUpsOverTempWarningTrap.name: lcUpsOverTempWarningTrap
lcUpsOverTempWarningTrap.description: An lcUpsOverTempWarningTrap signifies that the UPS has detected a excessive temperature condition.

lcUpsOverTempShutdownTrap.name: lcUpsOverTempShutdownTrap
lcUpsOverTempShutdownTrap.description: An lcUpsOverTempShutdownTrap signifies that the UPS has detected a excessive temperature condition and shut off the output.

lcUpsAlarmTrap.name: lcUpsAlarmTrap
lcUpsAlarmTrap.description: An Alarm condition has occurred and is being reported in the lcUpsAlarmTable.

lcUpsOutputOffTrap.name: lcUpsOutputOffTrap
lcUpsOutputOffTrap.description: An lcUpsOutputOffTrap is sent when the UPS turns all of its output off, either at the inverter or via a relay.

lcUpsOutputOffWarningTrap.name: lcUpsOutputOffWarningTrap
lcUpsOutputOffWarningTrap.description: An lcUpsOutputOffWarningTrap is sent when the lcUpsControlOutputOffDelay reaches the value of lcUpsControlOutputOffTrapDelay.

lcUpsOutputOnTrap.name: lcUpsOutputOnTrap
lcUpsOutputOnTrap.description: An lcUpsOutputOnTrap is sent when the UPS turns all of its output back on, either at the inverter or via a relay.

lcUpsOutputOnWarningTrap.name: lcUpsOutputOnWarningTrap
lcUpsOutputOnWarningTrap.description: An lcUpsOutputOnWarningTrap is sent when the lcUpsControlOutputOnDelay reaches the value of lcUpsControlOutputOnTrapDelay.

lcUpsUnixShutdownTrap.name: lcUpsUnixShutdownTrap
lcUpsUnixShutdownTrap.description: An lcUpsUnixShutodwnTrap is sent 2 seconds before the UPS is scheduled to perform a Unix Shutdown.

lcUpsUnixShutdownWarningTrap.name: lcUpsUnixShutdownWarningTrap
lcUpsUnixShutdownWarningTrap.description: An lcUpsUnixShutdownWarningTrap is sent when the lcUpsControlUnixShudownDelay reaches the value of lcUpsControlUnixShutdownTrapDelay.

lcUpsInputFreqErrorTrap.name: lcUpsInputFreqErrorTrap
lcUpsInputFreqErrorTrap.description: An ldUpsInputFreqErrorTrap signifies that the UPS has detected that input frequency is outside tolerable variance.

lcUpsDCOverVoltageShutdownTrap.name: lcUpsDCOverVoltageShutdownTrap
lcUpsDCOverVoltageShutdownTrap.description: An lcUpsDCOverVoltageShutdownTrap signifies that the UPS has detected that battery voltage is over the tolarable level.

lcUpsOutputOverVoltageTrap.name: lcUpsOutputOverVoltageTrap
lcUpsOutputOverVoltageTrap.description: An lcUpsOutputOverVoltageTrap signifies that the UPS has detected that the output voltage is too high.

lcUpsFuseBlownTrap.name: lcUpsFuseBlownTrap
lcUpsFuseBlownTrap.description: An lcUpsFuseBlownTrap is sent when the UPS's rectifier or DC capacitor fuse has failed.

lcUpsEmergencyPowerOffTrap.name: lcUpsEmergencyPowerOffTrap
lcUpsEmergencyPowerOffTrap.description: An lcUpsEmergencyPowerOffTrap signifies that the UPS has shut off output due to an emergency condition.

lcUpsControlPowerFailureTrap.name: lcUpsControlPowerFailureTrap
lcUpsControlPowerFailureTrap.description: An lcUpsControlPowerFailureTrap signifies a failure in the secondary control power.

lcUpsReversePowerTrap.name: lcUpsReversePowerTrap
lcUpsReversePowerTrap.description: An lcUpsReversePowerTrap signifies that output has been shut off due to a reverse power flow condition.

lcUpsPhaseRotationErrorTrap.name: lcUpsPhaseRotationErrorTrap
lcUpsPhaseRotationErrorTrap.description: An lcUpsPhaseRotationErrorTrap signifies a phase-rotation error in the bypass power.

lcUpsLoadOnBypassTrap.name: lcUpsLoadOnBypassTrap
lcUpsLoadOnBypassTrap.description: An lcUpsLoadOnBypassTrap signifies that the load has been transferred to bypass power.

lcUpsEmergencyXferToBypassTrap.name: lcUpsEmergencyXferToBypassTrap
lcUpsEmergencyXferToBypassTrap.description: An lcUpsEmergencyXferToBypassTrap signifies that the UPS has automatically tranferred the load to bypass power.

lcUpsInverterFaultTrap.name: lcUpsInverterFaultTrap
lcUpsInverterFaultTrap.description: An lcUpsInverterFaultTrap signifies that the UPS detected a problem with the Inverter.

lcUpsReceptOffTrap.name: lcUpsReceptOffTrap
lcUpsReceptOffTrap.description: An lcUpsReceptOffTrap is sent when the UPS turns an output receptacle off.

lcUpsReceptOffWarningTrap.name: lcUpsReceptOffWarningTrap
lcUpsReceptOffWarningTrap.description: An lcUpsReceptOffWarningTrap is sent when the lcUpsSwitchedReceptOffDelay reaches the value of lcUpsSwitchedReceptOffTrapDelay.

lcUpsReceptOnTrap.name: lcUpsReceptOnTrap
lcUpsReceptOnTrap.description: An lcUpsReceptOnTrap is sent when the UPS turns an output receptacle on.

lcUpsReceptOnWarningTrap.name: lcUpsReceptOnWarningTrap
lcUpsReceptOnWarningTrap.description: An lcUpsReceptOnWarningTrap is sent when the lcUpsSwitchedReceptOnDelay reaches the value of lcUpsSwitchedReceptOnTrapDelay.

lsUpsIdentFirmwareVersion.name: lsUpsIdentFirmwareVersion
lsUpsIdentFirmwareVersion.description: The firmware revision level of the UPS.

lsUpsCheckAirFilterTrap.name: lsUpsCheckAirFilterTrap
lsUpsCheckAirFilterTrap.description: An lsUpsCheckAirFilterTrap signifies that the programmed time interval for checking the air filter has passed and it is time to check the air filter.

lsUpsConfigBypassInstalled.name: lsUpsConfigBypassInstalled
lsUpsConfigBypassInstalled.description: Indicates if a bypass is installed in the UPS.

lsUpsOnBypass.name: lsUpsOnBypass
lsUpsOnBypass.description: Indicates that the UPS is currently on bypass.

lsUpsBypassFrequency.name: lsUpsBypassFrequency
lsUpsBypassFrequency.description: The current bypass frequency. (Unit of measure: Hertz)

lsUpsBypassNumLines.name: lsUpsBypassNumLines
lsUpsBypassNumLines.description: The number of bypass lines utilized in this device. This entry indicates the number of rows in the bypass table.

lsUpsBypassVoltage.name: lsUpsBypassVoltage
lsUpsBypassVoltage.description: The bypass voltage. (Unit of measure: Volt)

lsUpsBypassCurrent.name: lsUpsBypassCurrent
lsUpsBypassCurrent.description: The bypass current. (Unit of measure: Amp)

ldUpsDCOverVoltageShutdownTrap.name: ldUpsDCOverVoltageShutdownTrap
ldUpsDCOverVoltageShutdownTrap.description: An ldUpsDCOverVoltageShutdownTrap signifies that the UPS has detected that battery voltage is over the tolarable level.

ldUpsOutputShortShutdownTrap.name: ldUpsOutputShortShutdownTrap
ldUpsOutputShortShutdownTrap.description: An ldUpsOutputShortShutdownTrap signifies that the UPS has detected a short circuit across the output.

ldUpsLNReversedShutdownTrap.name: ldUpsLNReversedShutdownTrap
ldUpsLNReversedShutdownTrap.description: An ldUpsLNReversedShutdownTrap signifies that the UPS has detected that Line and Neutral have been reversed.

ldUpsImminentShutdownTrap.name: ldUpsImminentShutdownTrap
ldUpsImminentShutdownTrap.description: An ldUpsImminentShutdownTrap signifies that the UPS is about to turn off output power.

ldUpsInputFreqErrorTrap.name: ldUpsInputFreqErrorTrap
ldUpsInputFreqErrorTrap.description: An ldUpsInputFreqErrorTrap signifies that the UPS has detected that input frequency is outside tolerable variance.

ldUpsOutputOverVoltageTrap.name: ldUpsOutputOverVoltageTrap
ldUpsOutputOverVoltageTrap.description: An ldUpsOutputOverVoltageTrap signifies that the UPS has detected that the output voltage is too high.

ldUpsOutputUnderVoltageTrap.name: ldUpsOutputUnderVoltageTrap
ldUpsOutputUnderVoltageTrap.description: An ldUpsOutputUnderVoltageTrap signifies that the UPS has detected that the output voltage is too low.

ldUpsChargerFailedTrap.name: ldUpsChargerFailedTrap
ldUpsChargerFailedTrap.description: An ldUpsChargerFailedTrap signifies that the UPS has detected that the battery charger has failed.

ldUpsInputMaxVoltsSinceLastPoll.name: ldUpsInputMaxVoltsSinceLastPoll
ldUpsInputMaxVoltsSinceLastPoll.description: The maximum input voltage encountered since the object was last retrieved. Note: if there are multiple managers talking to the same agent, the use of this object needs to be coordinated.

ldUpsInputMinVoltsSinceLastPoll.name: ldUpsInputMinVoltsSinceLastPoll
ldUpsInputMinVoltsSinceLastPoll.description: The minimum input voltage encountered since the object was last retrieved. Note: if there are multiple managers talking to the same agent, the use of this object needs to be coordinated.

ldUpsOutputMaxVoltsSinceLastPoll.name: ldUpsOutputMaxVoltsSinceLastPoll
ldUpsOutputMaxVoltsSinceLastPoll.description: The maximum output voltage encountered since the object was last retrieved. Note: if there are multiple managers talking to the same agent, the use of this object needs to be coordinated.

ldUpsOutputMinVoltsSinceLastPoll.name: ldUpsOutputMinVoltsSinceLastPoll
ldUpsOutputMinVoltsSinceLastPoll.description: The minimum output voltage encountered since the object was last retrieved. Note: if there are multiple managers talking to the same agent, the use of this object needs to be coordinated.

lgUpsDCOverVoltageShutdownTrap.name: lgUpsDCOverVoltageShutdownTrap
lgUpsDCOverVoltageShutdownTrap.description: An lgUpsDCOverVoltageShutdownTrap signifies that the UPS has detected that battery voltage is over the nominal level.

lgUpsOutputShortShutdownTrap.name: lgUpsOutputShortShutdownTrap
lgUpsOutputShortShutdownTrap.description: An lgUpsOutputShortShutdownTrap signifies that the UPS has detected a short circuit across the output.

lgUpsLNReversedShutdownTrap.name: lgUpsLNReversedShutdownTrap
lgUpsLNReversedShutdownTrap.description: An lgUpsLNReversedShutdownTrap signifies that the UPS has detected that Line and Neutral have been reversed.

lgUpsInputUVOnStartupTrap.name: lgUpsInputUVOnStartupTrap
lgUpsInputUVOnStartupTrap.description: An lgUpsInputUVOnStartupTrap signifies that the UPS detected a low voltage condition upon system startup.

luSeries200InputMaxVoltsSinceLastPoll.name: luSeries200InputMaxVoltsSinceLastPoll
luSeries200InputMaxVoltsSinceLastPoll.description: The maximum input voltage encountered since the object was last retrieved. Note: if there are multiple managers talking to the same agent, the use of this object needs to be coordinated.

luSeries200InputMinVoltsSinceLastPoll.name: luSeries200InputMinVoltsSinceLastPoll
luSeries200InputMinVoltsSinceLastPoll.description: The minimum input voltage encountered since the object was last retrieved. Note: if there are multiple managers talking to the same agent, the use of this object needs to be coordinated.

luSeries200ConfigBypassInstalled.name: luSeries200ConfigBypassInstalled
luSeries200ConfigBypassInstalled.description: Indicates if a bypass is installed in the UPS.

luSeries200ConfigFrequencyChangerModel.name: luSeries200ConfigFrequencyChangerModel
luSeries200ConfigFrequencyChangerModel.description: Indicates whether this AP200 model is a frequency changer model.

luSeries200OnBypass.name: luSeries200OnBypass
